Happy Monday and that means it’s MOTW - Move of the Week - time! This week’s focus is on Obliques. The muscles that need just as much love as anything else because they help us bend and rotate! Having a former severe back injury myself I incorporate moves like this along with my regular exercise regime to ensure my body is stable and strong no matter how I move! Some days I go Advanced and some may be Beginner. The level doesn’t matter, the dedication does!Fitness Rx: 3 Moves for Any Level!
60s / side or 10x - 20x reps, 3 to 5 sets. 
1- Beginner 
2- Intermediate
3- Advanced
Live, Laugh, and Love your Body!
.

Hello fit fam!! I have an exciting announcement to share with you all! I’m honored to participate in this charity fundraiser this month to help American kids out there who need us. No child should go hungry in America but 9 million kids in the United States are living with hunger.  No Kid Hungry is ending childhood hunger by helping launch and improve programs that give all kids the healthy food they need to thrive.

Join me for my Get Fit livestream fundraiser this January as we make progress on our own health while raising the necessary funds to make No Kid Hungry a reality. A $10 donation can help provide 100 meals to kids!* 

Check out No Kid Hungry’s month-long Get Fit calendar to see when I will go live as well as other fitness, wellness and nutrition influencers participating in the campaign. Let’s band together to go live, get fit & give back!

*No Kid Hungry does not provide individual meals; your donations help support programs that feed kids. Learn more at NoKidHungry.org/OneDollar.

Christina XTina Jensen

💦I saw a new trend this am called cozy cardio and I must admit it really bothered me. 
.
Please take these trends, quick fix fitness tips and throw them away. Working out is hard. Working out also is not comfortable. It pushes us in an uncomfortable way which ironically is the best part of working out. It is a huge accomplishment and one to celebrate! There is nothing about it that is cozy or comfortable aside from the leggings or sports bra I wear. 
.
The simple truth is that when you embrace that it will be an uncomfortable process you will make progress, you will feel better and you will have more energy and confidence and much of that comes from overcoming the challenge. That work then translates into our everyday lives supporting the goal of feeling more comfortable physically, emotionally, spiritually, professionally, etc… Common… we know better so let’s be better. Don’t be afraid of hard work and all the struggle that comes with it. That’s what I am here for along with other fitness pros to help guide you in those struggles. Lean on us, ask questions, and don’t be afraid to try something that is challenging. With us, you’re in good company because WE GET IT! Now get out there and sweat for progress baby! 💦
.
.
📸 @urbanshots_ @lululemonstudio 
👟 @lululemon #lululemonambassador #thesweatlife #fitnessmotivation #friday #workhard #athomeworkouts #❌tina #trainwithtina
